years ago, a First Trust salesman bragged to colleagues about luring $13 mi=
llion in business from advisers at a big bank by dangling access to a perfo=
rmance coach. In another email later on, a managing director chided colleag=
ues, writing that =E2=80=9Cpay to play=E2=80=9D is =E2=80=9Cobviously illeg=
al but we have wholesalers=E2=80=9D=E2=80=94First Trust=E2=80=99s name for =
its salespeople=E2=80=94=E2=80=9Cdoing it repeatedly.=E2=80=9D If true, tha=
t could mean the everyday investors who bought the firm=E2=80=99s products =
